      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third party, like a title company, that holds your earnest money throughout the home-buying process. This keeps your deposit secure and prevents you from losing it if the deal falls apart for reasons outside of your control. The funds are only released to the seller once all conditions of the purchase agreement are met and the sale officially closes.",
