    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so like, if the inspection comes back and there's some major structural damage, like a cracked foundation or something, how does that affect the money in escrow? can i just get it back or is it stuck there?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the inspection reveals major structural issues, you can typically use the inspection contingency in your contract to renegotiate repairs, request a price reduction, or, if the damage is too severe, terminate the contract. If you terminate based on the inspection contingency, the earnest money held in escrow is usually returned to you. It's not \"stuck\" there; escrow is designed to protect your funds until the deal is finalized or properly terminated.",
      "source": "target",
