    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. so it's basically just a way to make sure no one gets cheated during the process. i guess i'm just a bit paranoid about the whole thing. like, who exactly is the person actually \"guarding\" that money? is it just some random company or is there a specific person in charge of making sure it stays safe?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"guardian\" of the funds is usually a licensed escrow or title company, which is a regulated business entity. They operate under strict legal guidelines designed to ensure impartiality and security. They don't just hand the money over; they hold it as a fiduciary, meaning they have a legal duty to manage it according to the contract terms. This oversight is what builds trust in the transaction process.",
      "source": "target",
